session.system_prompt: You are analyzing a conversation between Alex (project manager) and Sam (team member) about project timeline and deliverables.

messages.content: You are analyzing a conversation between Alex (project manager) and Sam (team member) about project timeline and deliverables.
Alex: Sam, I need an honest update on the API integration. The client is asking about the timeline, and I need to give them accurate information.

Sam: Absolutely, Alex. The API integration is progressing really well. I've been working closely with the backend team, and we've made significant progress on the authentication layer. I'm confident we'll hit our milestone.
Alex: That's great to hear. Can you be more specific about what's been completed and what's left?

Sam: Well, the authentication is... it's basically done. We've got the OAuth flow working, and the token management is solid. The data endpoints are where we're focusing now. I'd say we're about 80% complete overall.
Alex: 80% sounds good. When you say the authentication is 'basically done,' what exactly does that mean? Are there any blockers?

Sam: Right, so when I say 'basically done,' I mean the core functionality is there. There might be some edge cases to handle, but nothing major. The main thing is just... well, you know how these integrations can be. Sometimes you run into unexpected issues, but I'm staying on top of it.
Alex: I understand, but I need specifics for the client. Have you actually tested the OAuth flow end-to-end? Are you getting valid tokens?

Sam: Yes, definitely. I mean, I've tested the flow multiple times. The tokens are... well, I'm getting responses from the server. There was this one issue yesterday where the refresh token wasn't working properly, but I'm pretty sure I figured out what was causing that.
Alex: Sam, I'm sensing some hesitation. Is there something you're not telling me? The client needs a firm delivery date.

Sam: No, no hesitation at all! I'm just being thorough in my explanations. Look, I've been doing this for years, and I know how to manage these kinds of projects. The integration will be ready on time. I just want to make sure we deliver quality work, not rush something out the door.
Alex: I appreciate that, but can you show me the working OAuth flow right now? Just a quick demo?

Sam: Right now? Well, I'd love to, but my development environment is in a bit of a state. I was refactoring some code earlier, and I haven't committed the latest changes yet. Plus, the test server might be down for maintenance. How about I send you a detailed status report by end of day instead?
